│ THOUGHT: The assertion requires that either the instruction has no users or all of its users are marked as deleted. Since dropAllReferences clears operands but not users, some users     │
│ remain unmarked, triggering the assert. A safe approach without changing the assert is to proactively mark all instruction users of the to-be-removed instruction as deleted, ensuring    │
│ the invariant holds. This aligns with the delayed deletion design: users will be deleted later by BoUpSLP, and marking them satisfies the assert.                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ sed -i '2719a\      // Proactively mark instruction users as deleted to satisfy removal invariant.\n      for (Use &U : I->uses()) {\n        if (auto *UserI =                           │
│ dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser()))\n          DeletedInstructions.insert(UserI);\n      }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
